# fixture-signing.key

This Ed25519 private key exists ONLY to make the JSF signature block in
the L4-E golden CBOM JSON files deterministic. It has no production
purpose and is never rotated by design — rotating it would invalidate
all goldens.

## Derivation

The key is generated from a fixed seed:

    seed = SHA-256("cipherflag-golden-cbom-fixture-v1")
    priv = ed25519.NewKeyFromSeed(seed)

It is then written as a PEM block of type `PRIVATE KEY` whose body is
the 64-byte raw `ed25519.PrivateKey` (seed || public key) — the format
`NewFileSigner` reads in `internal/export/cbom/signer_file.go`. Note
this is NOT PKCS#8; the signer decodes the PEM and uses
`block.Bytes` directly as the 64-byte Ed25519 private key.

Anyone can recompute it. We check in the derived PEM only because
Go's test harness has no clean "generate-from-seed at test-load"
pattern.

## Constraints

- Do NOT reference this key from any non-test code path.
- Do NOT rotate this key — rotating invalidates `scope_rich.json`,
  `application_rich.json`, and `repo_rich.json` byte-for-byte.
- CI scanners that flag committed private keys: please allowlist this
  path.

## Where it's loaded

`internal/export/cbom/golden_test.go` (added in a later L4-E task) loads
it via `NewFileSigner`; the function is declared at
`internal/export/cbom/signer_file.go:18`.
